<figureCitation box="[337,369,266,290]" captionStart="Figures 18–26" captionStartId="34.[192,287,1820,1842]" captionTargetBox="[212,1410,225,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[204,1428,213,1789]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figures 18–26. Beltia, dorsal habitus. 18) Beltia angustomarginata, male. 19) Beltia awapita, male. 20) Beltia chiriquensis, female. 21) Beltia confusa, male. 22) Beltia gorgona, female. 23) Beltia herreri, male. 24–26) Beltia ledesmae, females. 24) Monochrome specimen. 25) Bicolored specimen. 26) Same female as (25) photographed with diffuser." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713509/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">23</figureCitation>
